definition.value: A host-coronavirus molecular interaction where the focus is the coronavirus process inside a host cell at the molecular level.

label.value: SARS-CoV-2 Nsp15 protein interaction with host protein

definition.value: A molecular interaction that has participant of the SARS-CoV-2 Nsp15 protein and a host protein
A coronavirus-host interaction by which the coronavirus enters the cytosol of a host cell
A COVID-19 serological diagnostic assay that tests the serum from the blood specimen to detect the antigen-antibody complex using light emission, which is generated from a chemical reaction.
a COVID-19 nucleic acid diagnostic assay using Next Genergation Sequence technology to detect virus RNA sequence.

a COVID-19 ELISA serological diagnostic assay is a kind of rapid test that  run the liquid sample along the surface of a pad with reactive molecules that show a visual positive or negative results. This testing dose not need for specialized and costly equipment.

A role taken by a chemical entity that binds to and inhibits the angiotensin II receptor type 1 (AT1) and thereby block the arteriolar contraction and sodium retention effects of renin–angiotensin system.

A role taken by a chemcial entity that inhibits the activity of angiotensin-converting enzyme, an important component of the renin–angiotensin system which converts angiotensin I to angiotensin II, and hydrolyses bradykinin. ACE inhibitor drugs are used primarily for the treatment of high blood pressure and heart failure by causing relaxation of blood vessels as well as a decrease in blood volume, which leads to lower blood pressure and decreased oxygen demand from the heart.
